 Detective Constable Alicia BeemingPicture: Supplied
Bitten by a spider or stung by a bee? Detective Alicia Beeming’s inconsistent excuses for not pitching up for court on Tuesday morning saw the Port Elizabeth Regional Court issue a warrant for her arrest.
The court heard that Beeming never attended any of her pre-sentence hearings with the probation officer, with one excuse for not attending being that she was bitten by a spider.
On Tuesday she claimed she could not be in court because she was stung by a bee.
Beeming, who was attached to the specialized gang unit,pleaded guilty in August to defeating the ends of justice after she had a personal relationship with a wanted gangster and concealed his whereabouts.

